=== 3. (L,K) SEPARABILITY ===
  low+mid non-flush PAUSE rows: 221;  with pred_tw==0: 31
  their (occ,age,cidle): {(3, 1, 3): 5, (4, 0, 3): 19, (4, 1, 3): 7}
  The architect's premise ('the low band has no tw=0 pause rows') is
  FALSE - there are 31. But EVERY one has cidle==3==floor, so they are
  explained by the floor and constrain L only by inequality. The
  conclusion (L,K unidentifiable) therefore STANDS, for a different
  reason. A tw=0 pause row with cidle 4 would break the ridge; none exists.

  2D map (D=cnt_next<=2&euCons floor=3 D0=onset), exact on FIT n=111:
